---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Support Our Work | LaTech Editorial Publishing"
  description="Support independent scholarship and public education. Your contribution helps us publish rigorous research and make knowledge accessible."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Support Our Work</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">
        Help us advance accessible scholarship and public education
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="narrow-content">
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Your Support Makes a Difference</h2>
        <p>
          Independent publishing requires resources. Unlike commercial publishers
          or institutions with large endowments, we rely on community support to
          sustain our operations. Your contribution helps us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Maintain editorial independence:</strong> Free from commercial
            and institutional pressures, we can publish work based solely on quality
            and contribution. Your support ensures we don't need to compromise our
            editorial standards for revenue.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Support emerging scholars:</strong> Through mentorship programs,
            writing workshops, and editorial guidance, we help graduate students and
            early-career researchers develop their voices and share their work.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Keep content accessible:</strong> We don't charge readers to access
            our content or authors to publish with us. Your support makes this
            open-access model sustainable.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Sustain rigorous review:</strong> Quality peer review and editorial
            support require time and expertise. Your contributions help us maintain
            these standards without passing costs to authors or readers.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Expand our reach:</strong> From SEO optimization to newsletter
            distribution to platform improvements, your support helps us reach more
            readers and have greater impact.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Every contribution, regardless of size, helps us advance our mission. Whether
          you're a researcher who values open access, a reader who benefits from our
          content, or someone who believes in the importance of accessible scholarship,
          your support makes a real difference.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>How Contributions Are Used</h2>
        <p>Your support directly funds:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Editorial operations and review processes:</strong> Ensuring quality
            and rigor in everything we publish
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Writer and researcher support programs:</strong> Resources, feedback,
            and mentorship for emerging scholars
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Technology and platform maintenance:</strong> Keeping our digital
            infrastructure accessible and functional
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Expanding reach and accessibility:</strong> SEO, distribution,
            and partnerships to extend our impact
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section donate-section">
        <h2>Make a Contribution</h2>
        <div class="donate-box">
          <p>
            We're currently setting up secure donation processing. In the meantime,
            we welcome contributions through several channels:
          </p>
          <ul style="text-align: left; max-width: 600px; margin: var(--spacing-lg) auto;">
            <li>
              <strong>Direct contact:</strong> Email us at <a href="mailto:donate@latecheditorialpublishing.com"
                >donate@latecheditorialpublishing.com</a> to discuss support options,
                including one-time contributions, recurring donations, or sponsorship
                opportunities
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>In-kind support:</strong> We also welcome in-kind contributions,
              such as editorial services, design work, technical expertise, or other
              professional services that support our operations
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Institutional partnerships:</strong> Universities, research
              institutions, and organizations interested in supporting our mission
              can contact us to discuss partnership opportunities
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            All contributions, whether financial or in-kind, help us advance our
            mission of making quality scholarship accessible to all. We're grateful
            for any support you can provide.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/contact/"
            class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us About Support</a
          >
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Other Ways to Support</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Share our content:</strong> Help spread quality scholarship by
            sharing articles and resources
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Subscribe to newsletter:</strong> Stay engaged with our work (coming
            soon)
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Submit your work:</strong> Contribute quality research, analysis,
            or commentary
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Volunteer:</strong> If you have skills in editing, design, or
            other areas, <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> to discuss opportunities
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Our Commitment to Transparency</h2>
        <p>
          We are committed to full transparency in how contributions are used.
          As we grow, we will publish annual reports detailing our finances,
          operations, and impact. Donors and supporters deserve to know how
          their contributions advance our mission.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>What we'll report:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Financial transparency:</strong> Detailed breakdowns of revenue
            and expenses, showing how contributions are allocated across editorial
            operations, platform maintenance, writer support, and other activities
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Impact metrics:</strong> Data on readership, geographic reach,
            content published, authors supported, and other indicators of our impact
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Operational updates:</strong> Information about new initiatives,
            partnerships, and developments in our work
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Challenges and lessons:</strong> Honest reporting on what's
            working, what isn't, and what we're learning as we grow
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We believe that transparency builds trust and accountability. As a
          mission-driven organization, we're accountable not just to our funders,
          but to our authors, readers, and the broader community we serve.
        </p>
        <p class="disclaimer">
          <strong>Nonprofit status:</strong> in formation / to be announced. We're
          working toward formal nonprofit status to ensure our mission remains
          protected and our operations remain transparent and accountable.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, #1e3a8a 100%);
    color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
    text-align: center;
    position: relative;
    clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 100% 85%, 0 100%);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .page-header::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(
      circle at top right,
      rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1) 0%,
      transparent 60%
    );
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .page-content {
    padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0 var(--spacing-2xl);
    animation: fadeIn 0.8s ease-out;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .content-section ul {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
    padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .content-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .content-section li::before {
    content: "â†’";
    color: var(--color-accent);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .donate-section {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      rgba(var(--color-bg-hue), var(--color-bg-sat), 95%, 1) 0%,
      rgba(255, 255, 255, 1) 100%
    );
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .donate-box {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .donate-box p {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .disclaimer {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-style: italic;
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: var(--spacing-md);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(10px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }
</style>
